/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
#
# Anchor to the crate root so the library's lockfile stays untracked
# but `fuzz/Cargo.lock` (conventional for a cargo-fuzz crate, which
# is a separate non-published binary member) can be committed.
/Cargo.lock
